α","translit":"logomachía","derivation":"from the same as G3054 (λογομαχέω);","strongs_def":"disputation about trifles (\"logomachy\")","kjv_def":"strife of words"},"G3004":{"id":"G3004","lemma":"λέγω","translit":"légō","derivation":"a primary verb;","strongs_def":"properly, to \"lay\" forth, i.e. (figuratively) relate (in words (usually of systematic or set discourse; whereas G2036 (ἔπω) and G5346 (φημί) generally refer to an individual expression or speech respectively; while G4483 (ῥέω) is properly to break silence merely, and G2980 (λαλέω) means an extended or random harangue)); by implication, to mean","kjv_def":"ask, bid, boast, call, describe, give out, name, put forth, say(-ing, on), shew, speak, tell, utter","pos":"verb","usage":"speak(61x), call(48x), tell(33x)"},"G3029":{"id":"G3029","lemma":"λίαν","translit":"lían","derivation":"of uncertain affinity;","strongs_def":"much (adverbially)","kjv_def":"exceeding, great(-ly), sore, very (+ chiefest)","pos":"adverb","usage":"exceeding(5x), greatly(4x), great(1x), sore(1x), very(1x)"},"G3036":{"id":"G3036","lemma":"λιθοβολέω","translit":"lithoboléō","derivation":"from a compound of G3037 (λίθος) and G906 (βάλλω);","strongs_def":"to throw stones, i.e. lapidate","kjv_def":"stone, cast stones","pos":"verb","usage":"stone(8x)"},"G3080":{"id":"G3080","lemma":"λύσις","translit":"lýsis","derivation":"from G3089 (λύω);","strongs_def":"a loosening, i.e. (specially), divorce","kjv_def":"to be loosed"}}